results.name: a(n) = product of non-powerful divisors d of n.
comment: Not multiplicative, for example a(2)*a(3) <> a(6). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jun 07 2011
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..16385
formula: a(1) = 1, a(p) = p, a(pq) = (pq)^2, a(pq...z) = (pq...z)^(2^(k-1)), a(p^k) = p, for p, q = primes, k = natural numbers, pq...z = product of k (k > 2) distinct primes p, q, ..., z.
example: For n = 12, set of such divisors is {2, 3, 6, 12}; a(12) = 1*2*3*6*12 = 432.
maple: isA001694 := proc(n) for p in ifactors(n)[2] do if op(2,p) = 1 then return false; end if; end do; return true; end proc:
A183103 := proc(n) local a,d; a := 1 ; for d in numtheory[divisors](n) do if not isA001694(d) then a := a*d; end if; end do; a ; end proc:
program: (PARI) A183103(n) = { my(m=1); fordiv(n, d, if(!ispowerful(d), m *= d)); m; }; \\ _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 07 2017
